From: knsol <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] fix: tolerate move_write_pointer failure in mount_sd_card

After a long recording, mount_sd_card() ends up failing with
"invalid file in move write pointer" — fs_stat on /SD:/audio/a01.txt
fails even though the FAT directory listing right above us showed
the file exists. Likely a FATFS quirk with the file size or some
intermediate state.

The good news is fs_mount itself succeeded ("SD card mounted
successfully" logged), and write_buffer was filled in by the snprintf
before fs_stat — so write_to_file later can still append to the file.

Demote move_write_pointer / move_read_pointer failures to LOG_WRN and
keep going. mount_sd_card returns 0 instead of -1 → main proceeds to
transport_start, pusher thread starts, audio writes resume.
---
diff --git a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/sdcard.c b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/sdcard.c
--- a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/sdcard.c
+++ b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/sdcard.c
@@ -107,9 +107,9 @@ int mount_sd_card(void)
     LOG_INF("new num files: %d", file_count);

     res = move_write_pointer(file_count);
     if (res) {
-        LOG_ERR("error while moving the write pointer");
-        return -1;
+        LOG_WRN("move_write_pointer failed (%d) — keeping path from snprintf, continuing", res);
+        res = 0;
     }

     move_read_pointer(file_count);
